<br>
*  I simply target my first mob to be messed<br>
*  Then start SoT<br>
*  Right after it starts (ie before it even takes hold) I target the next mob<br>
*  As soon as I get the message it took hold on mob 1 I stop and start the song immediately for Mob 2<br>
*  I then go target mob 3 immediately and wait for song to take effect on Mob 2.<br>
*  Etc...<br>
<br>
The point is you dont have to wait for SoT to take effect before you re-target.  You can target 1 mob, start song, target another mob, and song will still effect Mob 1.<br>
<br>
<br>
Also<br>
<br>
When messing 1 or 2 mobs only, you can mes them using this system, and then go back to fighting the main mob with group.  You dont have to wait for mes song to kick in.  Just make sure you dont &quot;twist&quot; until the mes takes effect.  <br>
<br>
You do have to be concerned with 2 things when using this method.<br>
<br>
1)  Watch out for resists.  If you get a resist you have to go back and re-mes the mob that resisted since you have a new mob targeted.<br>
<br>
2)  Make sure you dont kill song too fast.  When you mes your first mob, you have to stop &amp; start the mes song to get the second one.  Problem is if you do this too soon, youll stop your song before the mes takes hold on your first mob.<br>
<br>
